AGENT_SLUG-agent-integration.sh\\n    33→```\\n    34→\\n    35→The script is tailored to the specific agent's hook mechanism (not a generic template). Adapt the hook wiring section based on what Phase 2 discovered.\\n    36→\\n    37→**Script structure:**\\n    38→\\n    39→```bash\\n    40→#!/usr/bin/env bash\\n    41→set -euo pipefail\\n    42→\\n    43→AGENT_NAME=\\\"...\\\"\\n    44→AGENT_SLUG=\\\"...\\\"\\n    45→AGENT_BIN=\\\"...\\\"\\n    46→PROBE_DIR=\\\".entire/tmp/probe-${AGENT_SLUG}-$(date +%s)\\\"\\n    47→```\\n    48→\\n    49→**Required sections:**\\n    50→\\n    51→1. **Static checks** — Re-runnable binary/version/help checks\\n    52→2. **Hook wiring** — Create workspace-local config that intercepts hooks and dumps stdin JSON to `$PROBE_DIR/captures/<event-name>-<timestamp>.json`\\n    53→3. **Run modes:**\\n    54→   - `--run-cmd '<cmd>'` — Automated: launch agent, wait, collect\\n    55→   - `--manual-live` — Interactive: user runs agent manually, presses Enter\\n    56→4. **Capture collection** — List and pretty-print all payload files\\n    57→5. **Cleanup** — Restore original config (unless `--keep-config`)\\n    58→6. **Verdict** — PASS/WARN/FAIL per lifecycle event + COMPATIBLE/PARTIAL/INCOMPATIBLE\\n    59→\\n    60→### Phase 4: Execution & Analysis\\n    61→\\n    62→Run the script and analyze:\\n    63→\\n    64→1. **Execute**: `chmod +x scripts/test-$AGENT_SLUG-agent-integration.sh && scripts/test-$AGENT_SLUG-agent-integration.sh --manual-live`\\n    65→2. **For each captured payload**: show command, artifact path, decoded JSON\\n    66→3. **Lifecycle mapping**: native hook name → Entire EventType\\n    67→\\n    68→### Phase 5: Implementation One-Pager\\n    69→\\n    70→Write the research findings to `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE/AGENT.md` as a structured one-pager that the test-writer and implementer phases will use as their single source of agent-specific information.\\n    71→\\n    72→**Create the agent package directory first** (if it doesn't exist):\\n    73→\\n    74→```bash\\n    75→mkdir -p cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE\\n    76→```\\n    77→\\n    78→**Write the one-pager using this template:**\\n    79→\\n    80→```markdown\\n    81→# $AGENT_NAME — Integration One-Pager\\n    82→\\n    83→## Verdict: COMPATIBLE / PARTIAL / INCOMPATIBLE\\n    84→\\n    85→## Static Checks\\n    86→| Check | Result | Notes |\\n    87→|-------|--------|-------|\\n    88→| Binary present | PASS/FAIL | path |\\n    89→| Help available | PASS/FAIL | |\\n    90→| Version info | PASS/FAIL | version string |\\n    91→| Hook keywords | PASS/FAIL | keywords found |\\n    92→| Session keywords | PASS/FAIL | keywords found |\\n    93→| Config directory | PASS/FAIL | path |\\n    94→| Documentation | PASS/FAIL | URL |\\n    95→\\n    96→## Binary\\n    97→- Name: `$AGENT_BIN`\\n    98→- Version: ...\\n    99→- Install: ... (how to install if not present)\\n   100→\\n   101→## Hook Mechanism\\n   102→- Config file: `~/.config/$AGENT_SLUG/settings.json` (exact path)\\n   103→- Config format: JSON / YAML / TOML\\n   104→- Hook registration: ... (how hooks are declared — JSON objects, env vars, etc.)\\n   105→- Hook names and when they fire:\\n   106→  | Native Hook Name | When It Fires | Entire EventType |\\n   107→  |-----------------|---------------|-----------------|\\n   108→  | `on_session_start` | Agent session begins | `SessionStart` |\\n   109→  | ... | ... | ... |\\n   110→- Valid Entire EventTypes: `SessionStart`, `TurnStart`, `TurnEnd`, `Compaction`, `SessionEnd`, `SubagentStart`, `SubagentEnd`\\n   111→- Hook input (stdin JSON): ... (exact fields with example payload)\\n   112→\\n   113→## Transcript\\n   114→- Location: `~/.config/$AGENT_SLUG/sessions/<id>/transcript.jsonl`\\n   115→- Format: JSONL / JSON array / other\\n   116→- Session ID extraction: ... (from hook payload field or directory name)\\n   117→- Example entry: `{\\\"role\\\": \\\"user\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"...\\\"}`\\n   118→\\n   119→## Config Preservation\\n   120→- Keys to preserve when modifying: ... (or \\\"use read-modify-write on entire file\\\")\\n   121→- Settings that affect hook behavior: ...\\n   122→\\n   123→## CLI Flags\\n   124→- Non-interactive prompt: `$AGENT_BIN --prompt \\\"...\\\" --no-confirm`\\n   125→- Interactive mode: `$AGENT_BIN` (or \\\"not supported\\\")\\n   126→- Relevant env vars: ...\\n   127→\\n   128→## Gaps & Limitations\\n   129→- ... (anything that doesn't map cleanly)\\n   130→\\n   131→## Captured Payloads\\n   132→- See `.entire/tmp/probe-$AGENT_SLUG-*/captures/` for raw JSON captures\\n   133→```\\n   134→\\n   135→**Key points about the one-pager:**\\n   136→\\n   137→- The **Entire EventType mapping** (which native hook → which EventType) uses the event names learned from `agent-guide.md` in Phase 1. The researcher can do this mapping because it's a simple table — it doesn't need Entire source code.\\n   138→- Fill in every section with concrete values from Phases 2-4. Don't leave placeholders.\\n   139→- If a section doesn't apply (e.g., no transcript support), say so explicitly.\\n   140→- This file persists as development documentation — future maintainers will reference it.\\n   141→\\n   142→## Blocker Handling\\n   143→\\n   144→If blocked at any point (auth, sandbox, binary not found):\\n   145→\\n   146→1. State the exact blocker\\n   147→2. Provide the exact command for the user to run manually\\n   148→3. Explain what output to paste back\\n   149→4. Continue with provided output\\n   150→\\n   151→## Constraints\\n   152→\\n   153→- **No Go code.** This command produces a one-pager and test script only.\\n   154→- **Non-destructive.** All artifacts go under `.entire/tmp/` (gitignored). The one-pager goes in the agent package directory.\\n   155→- **Agent-specific scripts.** Adapt based on Phase 2 findings, not a generic template.\\n   156→- **Ask, don't assume.** If the hook mechanism is unclear, ask the user.\\n   157→- **Externa